description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Community Associate Specialist (Elderly Care) to join our friendly teams in rural west Kent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be part of a team who are dedicated to adult and elderly care, actively managing patients living with frailty and other complex conditions in their homes and hospitals and working closely with clinical, social and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in idyllic Tonbridge, you will provide expert support as part of our innovative Home Treatment Service, participating in comprehensive geriatric assessments and providing oversight of medical care for community hospital inpatients. You will support consultants, heads of service and operational leads to continue the development of the Home First service, contributing to strategic decision making. You’ll also provide leadership and mentorship of specialty doctors and advanced nurse practitioners (ANPs)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll need to be flexible, creative and ready to embrace new ways of working as we continue to invest in the community sector. In return we’ll offer you a fantastic role in a relaxed and welcoming environment that gives you the opportunity to expand your knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this is a full time post, candidates wanting to work less than full time or flexibly are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find out more about our clinical roles in west Kent here&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kentcht.nhs.uk/west-kent-clinical-recruitment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 7th December 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;George Noble 07818511664&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rachel Nicholls 07554 439581&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
